The course will give the basic knowledge about general principles and requirements of academic research and teaches to formulate research ideas, problems, hypotheses and tasks.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at giving the basic knowledge about academic research and to develop skills of academic writing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will:
- choose and focus their research interests and topics
- be able to formulate research purposes, research questions and hypotheses independently
- know about different sources and selection of data, analysis techniques used in academic research
- be familiar with the general style and language of research
- know the main rules for referencing others' work and composing a reference list
- be able to conduct and write a seminar paper, explain and defend choices made.
